 <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> be found guilty </t:quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዘሰ፡ ተርፈ፡ ሐመምኩ፡ ብሂሎ፡ በሐሰት፡ ይክስሶ፡ ጸላእቱ፡ ወእመ፡ ተረትዓ፡ ይኩን፡ እዳሁ፡ እዳ፡ ወንጀለኛ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> mais si quelqu’un reste chez lui en se disant faussement malade, que ses ennemis le défèrent au tribunal, et s’il est convaincu de fausseté, que sa main subisse le châtiment du traîte! </t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/><citedRange unit="page"> 113 l. 28-29 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 129 11-14 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">በዝኵሉ፡ ሶበ፡ ተረትአ፡ ነጸዩ፡ ሥዕርተ፡ ርእሱ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> Lorsqui’il fut certain de la culpabilité de ce Ṣâserguê {the person is inferred from the context} </t:quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Perruchon1893Zarayaeqob"/><citedRange unit="page"> 164 l. 12, 165 l. 1 (ed.); 164 l. 13, 165 l. 1 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተረትዐ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">taratǝʿa</t:quote></cit> <subc>III,1</subc> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይትረታዕ፡</foreign> «<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">être dressé, redressé, corrigé, justifié</t:quote></cit>» ― <foreign xml:lang="am">ተቀና፡</foreign> Ms. <ref type="BM" target="BNFabb217">BNFabb217</ref>, fol. 59r. <lb/>
